A nephew who was branded an 'ostentatious spendthrift' by his uncle will inherit his £800,000 Cornwall home - despite the elderly relative leaving a will to the contrary.

Before he died, aged 90, retired art historian, William 'Bill' Taylor, said his nephew Roger Taylor was 'the last person' he wanted to have Lower Manaton Farm, his grade-II listed long house in Callington.

The widower was adamant that his nephew would 'blow all the money' if he got his hands on it and that he wanted to leave £650,000 to charity - but now his wishes have finally been thwarted by an Appeal Court ruling.

