The nephew and his family were 
adamant that Mr Taylor had promised to leave them his home in return for
uprooting themselves from their home in Sheffield and moving south to care for him.

However, the pensioner insisted the 
only deal he ever struck with the couple was that they could live in the
house rent-free if they contributed towards the bills. To the day he died, he insisted he would be entirely within his rights to throw them out.

In
August last year, a year after Mr Taylor died, Judge Jeremy Griggs 
accepted the couple’s plea that an agreement had been struck by the 
uncle and awarded them the whole of Lower Manaton Farm, subject to inheritance tax.

